label: image data set analysis
definition: The process of deriving a data item from an image data set using computer algorithms. The produced data item can be an image data set, data measurement, or any other data item.
term editor: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9676-7377 ""Alexander D. Bartnik""|https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9990-8331 ""Alexander D. Diehl""|https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899 ""William D. Duncan""|https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2104-0568 ""Lucas M. Serra""|https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7245-3450 ""Lauren M. Wishnie""|https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9821-4132 ""Mackenzie T. Smith""

label: raw magnetic resonance image data set reconstruction
definition: A process that transforms raw magnetic resonance image data from an NMR/MRI machine into a reconstructed MR image data set.
output: reconstructed magnetic resonance image data set
